description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are looking for enthusiastic, energetic and dedicated RGN’s to work within our community nursing teams providing nursing care to patients in their own homes on a fixed term contract or secondment until 31/03/2021.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are passionate about delivering the best care for our patients and are looking for a rewarding role in a supportive and friendly environment, then we are looking for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The community teams offer a range of patient care activities including:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Complex Holistic Assessments&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Admission Avoidance&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Palliative End of Life Care&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Medication Administration – Transdermal, IV, Injections, Rectal&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;LTC Management&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Multi-Disciplinary Working&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Emotional Support / Advanced Communication with Nursing Care Needs&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Self-Care, Empowerment, Education&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Equipment provision&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Wound Care&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Pressure Ulcer Care&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nutrition Assessments&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Symptom Management&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continence Care – Catheterisation, Bowel Care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We work to provide care for people closer to home and care and compassion is at the heart of everything we do.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Imagine you&#39;re the patient - that&#39;s the simplest way to explain our approach to healthcare. We place the individual at the centre of everything we do, not just their condition and treatment. This means listening to what they have to say, recognising their needs and responding appropriately.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The community nursing teams work between the hours of 8am – 6pm across 7 days per week. We have a 30 hour temporary contract in the Bridgnorth locality, 37.5 hour contract in the Ludlow Locality and 18.75 hours in the Oswestry Locality.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We also have some exciting opportunities for band 5 community nurses to join a small team working with Shropshire care homes, residents and a wider multidisciplinary team around providing targeted support to care home residents to prevent avoidable admissions and enable people to receive care at home. This is also on a temporary contract until the 31.03.2021 and is weekdays only. Please call Donna Jones 07816235900 to discuss this further. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are interested in either of these opportunities above, we would love to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
